1
00:00:11,567 --> 00:00:12,667
Didn't the doctor say

2
00:00:12,733 --> 00:00:14,667
we could no longer
conceive again?

3
00:00:14,733 --> 00:00:16,300
Come on. Who knows?

4
00:00:16,367 --> 00:00:19,000
The lord might listen
to my prayer.

5
00:00:19,067 --> 00:00:22,333
You know, when that happens,
I have nothing else to ask for.

6
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:28,300
Up until, you prove to me that
you will follow all my wishes,

7
00:00:28,367 --> 00:00:31,133
only then,
will I let you out of this room.

8
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:35,033
Mommy, please!
I'm begging you, Mommy!

9
00:00:35,133 --> 00:00:36,100
Help me.

10
00:00:36,167 --> 00:00:37,067
I can no longer bear it.

11
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:39,967
Will I be like this forever?

12
00:00:40,933 --> 00:00:42,133
If it were always like this...

13
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,233
Mommy...

14
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:45,967
I wish I had been born
into a different family.

15
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:53,900
And who are you?

16
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:50,133
Whatever you think and feel,

17
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:53,333
please remember that
there are other people

18
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:58,433
who will listen to you
and will understand you.

19
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:01,233
We haven't met yet,

20
00:02:01,300 --> 00:02:08,133
but believe it or not,
I feel your pain.

21
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:11,000
So don't lose hope.

22
00:02:11,067 --> 00:02:14,033
Be strong, Mookie.

23
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:16,033
I'm here.

24
00:02:16,133 --> 00:02:18,933
I'm ready to listen.

25
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:25,433
Whoever you are...

26
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,633
thank you.

27
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:36,867
I felt better somehow.

28
00:02:39,367 --> 00:02:40,633
Come down here.

29
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:45,267
I'm asking you,
so you must answer.

30
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:48,367
Who are you and
what are you doing in my house?

31
00:02:52,867 --> 00:02:55,200
Have you been
a maid here before?

32
00:02:58,833 --> 00:03:00,967
So what are you doing here?

33
00:03:01,033 --> 00:03:03,000
Are you a thief?

34
00:03:03,067 --> 00:03:05,533
Did you come here to rob us?

35
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:09,933
Ma'am, no.

36
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:13,633
I'm Emma.
I'm your new laundrywoman.

37
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,300
Laundrywoman?

38
00:03:16,367 --> 00:03:18,567
I didn't hire any laundress.

39
00:03:18,633 --> 00:03:19,733
Oh, Ma'am! Ma'am!

40
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,500
Ma'am!

41
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:23,533
I hired her. That's Emma.

42
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:26,300
Without asking
for my permission?

43
00:03:27,533 --> 00:03:31,167
Didn't you tell me
to get a laundress?

44
00:03:31,233 --> 00:03:35,400
You told me to take care of it.
That's what I did.

45
00:03:35,467 --> 00:03:40,667
Then, I don't like what you did.

46
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:43,867
Sorry, Ma'am.

47
00:03:43,933 --> 00:03:47,633
I'm all alone.
There is so much to do, Ma'am.

48
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:49,900
I can't do everything
all at once.

49
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:56,333
What I hate most is when
you bring trash into my house

50
00:03:56,433 --> 00:03:57,700
without my knowledge.

51
00:04:00,567 --> 00:04:01,733
You can leave.

52
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:02,767
Oh, Ma'am!

53
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:03,900
Get out of my house!

54
00:04:03,967 --> 00:04:06,733
Ma'am, she still has
many clothes to launder.

55
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,400
Then finish it!

56
00:04:11,267 --> 00:04:13,300
Leave!

57
00:04:13,367 --> 00:04:14,367
Get lost!

58
00:04:28,233 --> 00:04:30,900
I wouldn't have
let you live here

59
00:04:30,967 --> 00:04:33,967
if my uncle hadn't asked me.

60
00:04:34,033 --> 00:04:35,933
There's no deposit,

61
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,900
and you gave only
half of the rent.

62
00:04:37,967 --> 00:04:40,733
Where can you find
something like that?

63
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:44,033
I know. I'm sorry, Miss Tina.

64
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:45,000
Don't worry.

65
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:47,567
I'll pay you
once I get my salary.

66
00:04:47,633 --> 00:04:49,167
I promise.

67
00:04:49,233 --> 00:04:51,200
Make sure of that.

68
00:04:51,267 --> 00:04:56,567
Ma'am, please don't fire me.
I badly need this job.

69
00:04:56,633 --> 00:04:57,967
Ma'am, I'm begging you.

70
00:04:58,033 --> 00:05:02,167
I already know
that we will never get along.

71
00:05:02,267 --> 00:05:07,633
You have only just arrived,
and you dare to enter my house.

72
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:11,667
I just looked upstairs to check
if there's some laundry left.

73
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:12,600
Yes, Ma'am.

74
00:05:12,667 --> 00:05:13,933
That's what she only did.

75
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:18,367
I'm not talking to you.

76
00:05:18,433 --> 00:05:20,033
So don't butt in.

77
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:21,800
Yes, I heard that.

78
00:05:23,133 --> 00:05:24,067
Ma'am...

79
00:05:24,133 --> 00:05:27,900
Ma'am, don't worry.
This won't happen again.

80
00:05:27,967 --> 00:05:30,800
Please don't fire me, Ma'am.

81
00:05:30,867 --> 00:05:32,300
Ma'am, please.

82
00:05:32,367 --> 00:05:34,533
My laundry is really piling up,
Ma'am.

83
00:05:34,633 --> 00:05:36,500
I'm all alone.
I can't manage it anymore.

84
00:05:36,567 --> 00:05:37,833
It's exhausting.

85
00:05:37,900 --> 00:05:39,833
Don't you feel bad for me?

86
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:44,933
Ma'am, do you want to wear
dirty clothes?

87
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,067
No!

88
00:05:46,133 --> 00:05:49,167
You know I'm allergic
to dirty things.

89
00:05:49,233 --> 00:05:51,600
That's what I'm saying.

90
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:52,667
Ma'am...

91
00:05:52,733 --> 00:05:55,200
Ma'am, please, I promise
this won't happen again.

92
00:05:55,267 --> 00:05:57,033
I won't go inside.

93
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:58,933
I don't want to see your face.

94
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:02,633
Ma'am, please.
I badly need this job.

95
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:08,800
If only
I don't need a laundress,

96
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:11,200
I won't accept you.

97
00:06:11,267 --> 00:06:16,067
So make sure
you don't come into my house.

98
00:06:16,133 --> 00:06:17,900
Once you do that...

99
00:06:19,367 --> 00:06:21,900
you're fired.

100
00:06:22,933 --> 00:06:23,833
Yes, Ma'am.

101
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:26,267
Thank you, Ma'am.

102
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:31,267
See? I told you.

103
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:55,033
Mommy.

104
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:58,667
You know I feel better now.

105
00:06:58,733 --> 00:07:02,000
I can move my legs a little now.

106
00:07:02,067 --> 00:07:03,300
But...

107
00:07:05,233 --> 00:07:07,033
they still hurt.

108
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:10,833
That's why
it's hard to move them.

109
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:13,500
So, Mommy, can I...

110
00:07:16,967 --> 00:07:19,433
Don't be stubborn, Mookie.

111
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,933
I won't give you what you want

112
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:26,133
because you still
haven't learned your lesson.

113
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:31,100
Oh, by the way,
I have something for you.

114
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:37,267
So, I bought you books,
arts and crafts,

115
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:39,600
and coloring books.

116
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:40,600
So, you see?

117
00:07:41,633 --> 00:07:43,567
You have many things to do.

118
00:07:43,633 --> 00:07:45,567
You won't get bored.

119
00:07:45,633 --> 00:07:49,500
And this is something special.

120
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,267
Do you like it?

121
00:08:04,967 --> 00:08:06,700
Thank you, Mommy.

122
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,733
Isn't that Emma?

123
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:05,367
What?
Where?

124
00:09:06,167 --> 00:09:06,767
There!

125
00:09:06,833 --> 00:09:07,933
That's Emma!

126
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:10,533
- Hey, Mister, Mister, stop.
- Emma!

127
00:09:12,433 --> 00:09:14,033
Aren't you from work?

128
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,667
What? How is it?

129
00:09:15,733 --> 00:09:17,367
Hey, Emma.

130
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:20,367
Why doesn't your employer
let her daughter out?

131
00:09:20,433 --> 00:09:21,733
Is Olive strict?

132
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:25,233
Yes, and what's
her daughter's illness?

133
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:28,833
I'm sorry
I can't answer your questions.

134
00:09:28,933 --> 00:09:30,767
I'll go home now.
I still need to cook, Mom.

135
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:32,433
I'll go with you.
Wait for me, hey!

136
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:34,267
Bye, Besties. See you tomorrow.

137
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:36,367
- Okay.
- Wait! Emma!

138
00:09:36,433 --> 00:09:38,533
- Hey, let's have a drink.
- What's wrong with her?

139
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,333
Emma! Dear.

140
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:42,767
Hey, why do you look like
someone borrowed

141
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:43,867
a million pesos from you?

142
00:09:43,933 --> 00:09:45,033
What happened?

143
00:09:45,100 --> 00:09:47,867
I almost lost my job earlier,
Mom.

144
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:48,967
What?

145
00:09:49,033 --> 00:09:51,633
What did you do?
Why did your employer get mad?

146
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:57,133
I went to her daughter's room.

147
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,400
What? I can't understand.

148
00:09:58,467 --> 00:10:01,433
She got mad because you went
to her daughter's room?

149
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:06,300
Maybe she's protecting
her child.

150
00:10:06,367 --> 00:10:07,867
She's sickly, they said.

151
00:10:07,933 --> 00:10:08,800
Don't worry.

152
00:10:08,867 --> 00:10:11,467
I'll talk to Ma'am Olive
when I see her.

153
00:10:11,533 --> 00:10:12,867
I'll try to get
on her good side.

154
00:10:12,933 --> 00:10:16,467
Mom, no, you don't have to.

155
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:18,033
You don't have
to stoop that low.

156
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:20,767
And Ma'am Olive might
even get madder at me.

157
00:10:20,833 --> 00:10:22,367
Gosh, you.

158
00:10:22,433 --> 00:10:24,700
You really don't trust me.

159
00:10:24,767 --> 00:10:29,200
Ma'am Olive and I will get along
once I talk to her.

160
00:10:29,267 --> 00:10:32,033
Mom, Ma'am Olive is different.

161
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:35,800
Dear, you only need
to be sweet with her.

162
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:39,833
She's grumpy
because her daughter is sickly.

163
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:47,233
It's really hard for a mother
to take care of her sick child.

164
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:50,500
You would really rather
be the one to get sick.

165
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:55,667
You would really do everything
to make your child better.

166
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:59,767
A mother will do anything.

167
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:02,000
Mom?

168
00:11:02,967 --> 00:11:04,700
Why? Are you like that too?

169
00:11:08,033 --> 00:11:09,900
Mom? Mom?

170
00:11:11,367 --> 00:11:12,800
What did you say?

171
00:11:12,867 --> 00:11:15,433
Was I like that before?
Was I also sickly?

172
00:11:16,633 --> 00:11:17,767
Oh, you?

173
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:18,767
Yes.

174
00:11:21,033 --> 00:11:26,067
I went to almost all churches
and prayed for you to get well.

175
00:11:26,133 --> 00:11:30,067
That's why when you gave birth
prematurely, I was so scared.

176
00:11:31,133 --> 00:11:34,100
If Kayla was alive now,

177
00:11:34,167 --> 00:11:36,233
she would definitely be sickly,
too.

178
00:11:52,233 --> 00:11:53,800
Flor?

179
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:55,567
Yes?

180
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:57,633
Do we have a new helper?

181
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:01,533
I think I heard
an unfamiliar voice.

182
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:04,767
Yes, we do. Her name's Emma.
Our new laundress.

183
00:12:06,533 --> 00:12:07,467
Emma?

184
00:12:14,867 --> 00:12:16,200
Oh.

185
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:21,433
Maybe she read what I wrote.

186
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:22,533
What did you say?

187
00:12:24,667 --> 00:12:25,700
Nothing.

188
00:12:25,767 --> 00:12:26,900
Nothing, Flor.

189
00:12:29,133 --> 00:12:30,600
Flor...

190
00:12:31,767 --> 00:12:32,900
can I ask a favor?

191
00:12:32,967 --> 00:12:34,300
What is it?

192
00:12:34,367 --> 00:12:38,533
Can you let me out
just for a bit?

193
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:42,067
Just a bit,
after mommy leaves.

194
00:12:42,133 --> 00:12:43,733
Mookie.

195
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:46,667
I don't want to lose my job,
please.

196
00:12:46,733 --> 00:12:48,100
Oh, you.

197
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:51,300
Well, just stay here.
I'll just bring this down.

198
00:13:18,367 --> 00:13:22,433
Emma, how are you?

199
00:13:22,533 --> 00:13:24,733
I almost lost hope.

200
00:13:25,767 --> 00:13:29,900
I thank God for giving me hope
through your message.

201
00:13:44,967 --> 00:13:48,533
Thank you
for making me feel better.

202
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:52,833
I hope that one day,
I'll meet you in person.

203
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:57,133
And hopefully,
I can comfort you.

204
00:13:57,233 --> 00:13:59,967
And I can make you smile.

205
00:14:03,367 --> 00:14:04,133
Emma?

206
00:14:08,933 --> 00:14:10,000
Ma'am?

207
00:14:10,067 --> 00:14:11,567
What are you reading?

208
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,300
Nothing, Ma'am.

209
00:14:24,367 --> 00:14:27,500
Just a list of things I'll buy
at the market later.

210
00:14:29,133 --> 00:14:34,900
If you have anything else to do,
can you do it after work?

211
00:14:35,967 --> 00:14:41,267
And I'm warning you,
don't come into my house again.

212
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:45,233
Yes, Ma'am.

213
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,367
Oh, by the way,

214
00:14:48,433 --> 00:14:51,700
you did a good job with the
laundry and ironing yesterday.

215
00:14:51,767 --> 00:14:55,733
Look, I'm wearing the clothes
you washed and ironed.

216
00:14:56,800 --> 00:15:02,600
Keep it up, and we'll get along
if you follow everything I want.

217
00:15:04,133 --> 00:15:05,633
Thank you, Ma'am.

218
00:15:55,533 --> 00:15:56,700
Is that her?

219
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:34,700
Emma!

220
00:16:36,167 --> 00:16:37,533
Could that be her?

221
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:40,500
The one I saw in the park?

222
00:16:45,567 --> 00:16:47,467
Wait, I think that's her!

223
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:52,533
Hush, my dear

224
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:56,367
Come here

225
00:16:56,433 --> 00:17:03,300
Sleep among the stars

226
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:15,967
Flor.

227
00:17:17,133 --> 00:17:18,333
You're awake now.

228
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:22,800
Flor, is Emma still here?

229
00:17:22,867 --> 00:17:25,167
Yes, but she's almost done
ironing clothes.

230
00:17:25,233 --> 00:17:26,833
She'll go home in a bit.

231
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:27,733
Wait.

232
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:29,900
Why did you ask?

233
00:17:29,967 --> 00:17:31,467
Nothing.

234
00:17:31,533 --> 00:17:32,400
Okay.

235
00:17:32,467 --> 00:17:34,600
I'll bring this
to your mommy's room.

236
00:17:34,667 --> 00:17:35,867
I'll leave you for now.

237
00:17:57,233 --> 00:17:59,567
I want to see Emma.

238
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:24,233
Here's the medicine
you asked me to get.

239
00:18:26,467 --> 00:18:27,367
Good.

240
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:29,967
Is this everything?

241
00:18:30,033 --> 00:18:31,167
Yes.

242
00:18:31,233 --> 00:18:32,833
Thank you, Astrid.

243
00:18:43,167 --> 00:18:45,633
Olive, does Mookie
really need that?

244
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:46,667
That's steroids.

245
00:18:46,733 --> 00:18:49,400
At higher doses,
the effects are bad.

246
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:53,133
You can now leave.

247
00:19:02,367 --> 00:19:03,900
Madam! Madam!

248
00:19:03,967 --> 00:19:05,333
Madam Beautiful!

249
00:19:07,167 --> 00:19:08,433
Madam Beautiful!

250
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:11,167
Who are you?
And what do you need?

251
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:12,633
Oh, gosh.

252
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:15,067
You're probably Madam Olive.

253
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:03,900
You're so beautiful.

254
00:20:05,833 --> 00:20:07,867
Don't touch me!

255
00:20:07,933 --> 00:20:09,033
Who are you?

256
00:20:09,100 --> 00:20:09,933
Oh!

257
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:13,600
I'm your laundress' mother.
Emma.

258
00:20:14,767 --> 00:20:17,367
Now I know who she takes after.

259
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:19,900
Madam.

260
00:20:19,967 --> 00:20:22,800
I have something to ask you.

261
00:20:22,867 --> 00:20:29,400
Please forgive whatever
my daughter has done.

262
00:20:29,467 --> 00:20:32,200
You know, she's hardworking
and persistent,

263
00:20:32,267 --> 00:20:33,933
and she's not a gossiper.

264
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:35,833
She takes after me.

265
00:20:37,433 --> 00:20:39,400
Is that all you're going to say?

266
00:20:39,467 --> 00:20:40,500
Yes.

267
00:20:40,567 --> 00:20:41,900
Then we're done here.

268
00:20:41,967 --> 00:20:42,733
Go.

269
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:46,933
Oh, Madam, I'll teach you
to play cards if you're bored.

270
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:55,067
She's beautiful...

271
00:20:57,133 --> 00:20:58,333
but so grumpy.

272
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:27,567
Hey, Emma.

273
00:21:27,633 --> 00:21:30,533
Where are you going? Why?
Did you forget something?

274
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:33,700
I hear someone screaming.

275
00:21:33,767 --> 00:21:36,100
No, that's nothing.
You can leave now.

276
00:21:36,167 --> 00:21:37,667
I still have a lot to do.

277
00:21:37,733 --> 00:21:39,033
See you tomorrow.

278
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:41,633
Thank you.

279
00:21:47,467 --> 00:21:48,733
Mookie?

280
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:50,400
What are you doing there?

281
00:21:50,467 --> 00:21:51,300
Mommy...

282
00:21:51,367 --> 00:21:52,433
You wanted to go out,
didn't you?

283
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:55,033
- No, Mommy.
- You never learn!

284
00:21:55,100 --> 00:21:56,400
You'll get what you deserve!

285
00:21:56,467 --> 00:21:57,533
Mommy, no!

286
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:59,533
- No!
- Didn't I tell you?

287
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:00,467
Mommy, no!

288
00:22:00,533 --> 00:22:03,300
You're always
giving me headaches!

289
00:22:03,367 --> 00:22:05,667
You promised you'd behave!

290
00:22:05,733 --> 00:22:08,733
You're lying again!

291
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:11,533
You deserve to be punished!
Come here!

292
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:15,400
You deserve it!

293
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:18,767
You deserve it
because you're stubborn!

294
00:22:18,833 --> 00:22:21,967
- Mommy!
- You never learn!

295
00:22:22,033 --> 00:22:25,433
Mommy, it hurts!

296
00:22:29,233 --> 00:22:32,433
When you feel like
everything is dark,

297
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:34,867
just look up at the sky.

298
00:22:34,933 --> 00:22:37,567
You will see at least one star.

299
00:22:37,633 --> 00:22:39,933
I feel better.

300
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:43,967
It's like having
a mom who hugs me.

301
00:22:44,033 --> 00:22:47,367
Can I treat you like my mother?

302
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:50,467
Would you agree?

303
00:22:50,533 --> 00:22:53,433
I don't understand.
Mookie isn't related to me.

304
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:57,833
But why do I feel hurt
every time I hear Mookie cry?

305
00:22:57,900 --> 00:23:01,300
Why? Why is it so painful?

306
00:23:01,367 --> 00:23:03,733
Mommy,
why are my legs like this?

307
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:07,567
Unfortunately, your infection
is getting worse.

308
00:23:08,867 --> 00:23:10,033
It hurts!

309
00:23:10,100 --> 00:23:11,433
Mommy!

310
00:23:11,500 --> 00:23:12,700
Mookie?

311
00:23:12,767 --> 00:23:16,467
Do you know what could happen
if it gets worse?

312
00:23:16,533 --> 00:23:17,733
What?

313
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:19,600
Your leg will be amputated.
